        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:07PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 506 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Alder Springs, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alder Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
